The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has declared Governor Samuel Ortom winner of the Benue state governorship election. PDP’s Ortom polled a total of 434,473 votes to defeat Barrister Emmanuel Jime of APC who scored 345,155 votes to come second. Ex-Ambassadors seek cancellation of Benue supplementary election PDP will win presidential election overwhelmingly in 2019 - Ortom I'm certain of victory — Ortom